        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">A reanimation spell would be really cool, actually. Being masters of the dead it would fit right in.</P><P>It would summon that mob to be your pet, the pet would have a total of maybe half or 1/4 its HP in life, and would simply poof after a minute (to line up with VI's Anti-Solo Vision<sup>tm</sup>, but not cost too much mana. It would be a level 50+ spell, since that's where we really need the work on our pets (or so I hear), and would be castable on just about any corpse there is except mobs with greater than X total HP (so as to stop people from reanimating named dragons in WW or ToV and using them as pets).</P><P>The thing about it is that there would have to be a corpse there to reanimate, meaning the corpse would still have to have something on it in terms of a small item or something.. or maybe they'd make empty corpses remain there for a half a minute or so after being completely looted so as to allow this, and have it cost an equivalent of the level 50 pets in bone chips, plus a cheap gem. (Peridots are NOT cheap.)</P><P>Maybe then they'd allow pets on raids.. when they knew your pets hit just as hard as the mobs did, but only lasted the duration of the fight so as not to run around getting you all killed afterwards.</P><P>Summoning a mob as your pet can certainly be done. Ask any mage. "Reanimating" the corpse of a dead mob is likely difficult, but not impossible.</P><P>-- Rendrac</P><P><table><td style=filter:glow(color=maroon strength=2);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 face=Verdana, sans-serif><i>Rendrac D'Vith regards you indifferently -- he appears to be a taxi.</i></font></td></table><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
