        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I can kinda sorta half-ass understand why Verant doesn't wnat us to be able to land normal lifetaps on certain mobs, but there's really zero possibility of necros being able to do any significant damage to most of the uber mobs in the game just by using lifetaps.</P><P>What I'd suggest is that they keep the old uber mobs with 32k hp or less immune to DD lifetaps, but make ALL mobs vulnerable to DoT lifetaps. There is ablsolutely no way that necros could exploit any uber mob just by casting DoT lifetaps on them.</P><P>This is what should have been done in the first place. I really never could understand the logic behind making DoT lifetaps resistable.</P><P>---This sig will no longer drop in game.---<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
